Author: iovtoken
Title: [ANN][ICO] IOV - The first DNS for Blockchains
Body: IOV - THE FIRST DNS FOR BLOCKCHAINS  Isabella Dell (CTO IOV & Former Chief System Architect of LISK ) and Ethan Frey (Previously 3rd engineer at Tendermint/Cosmos building the light client, SDK, and refining the IBC protocol) brings years of experience in the blockchain industry as a software engineer  PARIS (April 11, 2018)‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäIOV SAS, a blockchain startup that is providing a universal protocol for blockchains and wallet users, announced today that Ethan Frey has joined the company as Lead Developer. He will be in charge of the development of all backend coding of the IOV features, like the Blockchain Name Service and the [Suspicious link removed]munication Protocol.  Frey is a polymath software developer, that has been working on next-generation blockchains since late 2016. He has been interested in distributed systems and cryptography since his undergrad at Caltech and spent many years building backend systems for web applications in a variety of languages.  ‚ÄúI am excited to apply my experience to make a secure, reliable and user-friendly blockchain framework here at IOV‚Äù, said Ethan.  From optimizing real-time queries on terabytes of data to auto-scaling microservices and messaging queues, Ethan has focused on reliability, security, and stable production deployments. He has embraced blockchain as a decentralized solution to security and trust since discovering Ethereum in 2015. He then joined Tendermint/Cosmos full-time as the third engineer in January 2017, building the light client, SDK, and refining the IBC protocol.  ‚ÄúIt is with great pride that we welcome Ethan on board. His technical skill set is well respected in many [Suspicious link removed]munities and I have full faith in his abilities to help bring IOV‚Äôs vision to life‚Äù, added Isabella Dell, IOV co-founder and CTO of the company.  About IOV:  IOV is a Paris-based blockchain startup that provides a universal protocol for blockchains and wallet users. IOV solves the problem of complexity, human error and lack of interoperability when exchanging digital assets on multiple blockchains. IOV provides the [Suspicious link removed]munication Protocol that enables autonomous blockchains to be accessed efficiently. Additionally, IOV provides the Blockchain Name Service, the first DNS for all participating blockchains.  For more information, visit IOV - DNS FOR BLOCKCHAINS . Also, join us on our Telegram Channel  IOV - TELEGRAM CHANNEL
